cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.LG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a type-assignment system for the linear lambda calculus, which is a topic closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the representation of boolean circuits and natural numbers using the linear lambda calculus, which are topics related to programming languages.
- cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) is another likely category as the paper presents a new type-assignment system and discusses its properties, which are topics related to theoretical computer science.
- cs.LG (Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of Hereditarily Finite Permutations, which are a topic related to machine learning and neural networks.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the computational cost of the cut-elimination procedure in the new type-assignment system.
